<subSubSection id="C30F653F5D61FFBAFF63B95A327A878B" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D61FFBAFF63B95A374D870B" blockId="39.[189,928,1526,1621]" box="[189,310,1595,1621]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D61FFBAFF63B95A374D870B" bold="true" box="[189,310,1595,1621]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D61FFBAFF63B90C327A878B" blockId="39.[189,1398,1645,1749]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Rather small (about 
<quantity id="4CED9B515D61FFBAFE6EB90C347587D6" box="[432,526,1645,1672]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
) species with 1 pair of vertical bristles, broad face, brown basal antennal segments, postpedicel having long dorsoapical extension, brownish palpus, katepisternum largely shining, brownish yellow legs, pale halteres and finely infuscate wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
