</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D6EFFB5FF63BE6A342E807B" blockId="40.[189,1398,267,376]" box="[189,597,267,293]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading id="D0E281D85D6EFFB5FF63BE6A342E807B" bold="true" box="[189,597,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FF63BE6A342E807B" bold="true" box="[189,597,267,293]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Habitat and seasonal occurrence</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D6EFFB5FF63BE5832A88026" blockId="40.[189,1398,267,376]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Only found on white sandy beaches or in mangroves with at least sandy patches; rarely in the burrows of Ghost crabs, 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FEA9BE3C37A48029" box="[375,479,349,375]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Ocypode" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FEA9BE3C37A48029" box="[375,479,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Ocypode</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. Flight period is from October and December (most records).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F653F5D6EFFB5FF63BEFF3434832D" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D6EFFB5FF63BEFF375480E6" blockId="40.[189,303,414,440]" box="[189,303,414,440]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading id="D0E281D85D6EFFB5FF63BEFF375480E6" bold="true" box="[189,303,414,440]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FF63BEFF375480E6" bold="true" box="[189,303,414,440]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45D6EFFB5FF63BEAD3434832D" blockId="40.[189,1399,460,628]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FDDCBEAC34DD80B9" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1851" box="[514,678,461,487]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculifera">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FDDCBEAC34DD80B9" box="[514,678,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. speculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group 
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FD25BEAC354780B8" box="[763,828,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455D6EFFB5FC9DBEAD359680B9" author="Chvala" box="[835,1005,460,487]" firstAuthor="Chvala" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="55 - 138" refId="ref68026" refString="Chvala M. 1977. Revision of Palaearctic species of the genus Chersodromia Walk. (Diptera, Empididae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 39: 55 - 138." type="journal article" year="1977">Chvála (1977)</bibRefCitation>
but, actually, is closely related to three species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FEA1BE91345C8354" authorityName="Walker, 1849:" authorityYear="1157" box="[383,551,496,522]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FEA1BE91345C8354" box="[383,551,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Chersodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry id="F30276245D6EFFB5FD35BE9135AB8354" box="[747,976,496,522]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455D6EFFB5FC3FBE9132E08354" author="Grootaert P." box="[993,1179,496,522]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="235 - 244" part="128" refId="ref68881" refString="Grootaert P. 1992. New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea. Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie 128: 235 - 244." title="New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea" type="journal article" year="1992">Grootaert 1992</bibRefCitation>
). All these species differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FE94BD72346B8373" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[330,528,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FE94BD72346B8373" box="[330,528,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by pale yellowish (
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FCDEBD72322C8373" authority="Grootaert, 1992" authorityName="Grootaert" authorityYear="1992" box="[768,1111,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipyga">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FCDEBD7235EA8373" box="[768,913,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. flavipyga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455D6EFFB5FC44BD72322C8373" author="Grootaert P." box="[922,1111,531,557]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="235 - 244" part="128" refId="ref68881" refString="Grootaert P. 1992. New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea. Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie 128: 235 - 244." title="New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea" type="journal article" year="1992">Grootaert, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) or yellowish-white (
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FA82BD723707830E" authority="Grootaert" authorityName="Grootaert" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micra">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FA82BD72377A830E" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. micra</emphasis>
Grootaert
</taxonomicName>
) to pale whitish (
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375D6EFFB5FD93BD5635DC830E" authority="Grootaert, 1992" authorityName="Grootaert" authorityYear="1992" box="[589,935,566,593]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chersodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripyga">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65D6EFFB5FD93BD563498830E" box="[589,739,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. nigripyga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455D6EFFB5FD35BD5735DC830E" author="Grootaert P." box="[747,935,566,592]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="235 - 244" part="128" refId="ref68881" refString="Grootaert P. 1992. New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea. Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie 128: 235 - 244." title="New species of the genus Chersodromia Walker (Diptera Empidoidea Hybotidae) from the northern coast of Papua New Guinea" type="journal article" year="1992">Grootaert, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) palpus and by the lack of a presutural supra-alar (= posthumeral) bristle.
</paragraph>
